      • createCommands

        public void createCommands​(Collection<StorageCommand> commands,
                           ReadableTransactionState txState,
                           StorageReader storageReader,
                           CommandCreationContext commandCreationContext,
                           ResourceLocker locks,
                           long lastTransactionIdWhenStarted,
                           TxStateVisitor.Decorator additionalTxStateVisitor,
                           PageCursorTracer cursorTracer,
                           MemoryTracker transactionMemoryTracker)
                    throws KernelException
        Description copied from interface: StorageEngine
        Generates a list of commands representing the changes in the given transaction state (state. The returned commands can be used to form CommandsToApply batches, which can be applied to this storage using StorageEngine.apply(CommandsToApply, TransactionApplicationMode). The reason this is separated like this is that the generated commands can be used for other things than applying to storage, f.ex replicating to another storage engine.
        Specified by:
        createCommands in interface StorageEngine
        Parameters:
        commands - Collection to put commands into.
        txState - ReadableTransactionState representing logical store changes to generate commands for.
        storageReader - StorageReader to use for reading store state during creation of commands.
        commandCreationContext - CommandCreationContext to use for do contextualized command creation e.g. id allocation.
        locks - ResourceLocker can grab additional locks. This locks client still have the potential to acquire more locks at this point. TODO we should try to get rid of this locking mechanism during creation of commands The reason it's needed is that some relationship changes in the record storage engine needs to lock prev/next relationships and these changes happens when creating commands The EntityLocker interface is a subset of Locks.Client interface, just to fit in while it's here.
        lastTransactionIdWhenStarted - transaction id which was seen as last committed when this transaction started, i.e. before any changes were made and before any data was read.
        additionalTxStateVisitor - any additional tx state visitor decoration.
        cursorTracer - underlying page cursor tracer
        transactionMemoryTracker - to report allocations to
        Throws:
        TransactionFailureException - if command generation fails or some prerequisite of some command didn't validate, for example if trying to delete a node that still has relationships.
        CreateConstraintFailureException - if this transaction was set to create a constraint and that failed.
        ConstraintValidationException - if this transaction was set to create a constraint and some data violates that constraint.
        KernelException - on known errors while creating commands.

        protected TransactionApplierFactoryChain applierChain​(TransactionApplicationMode mode)
        Provides a TransactionApplierFactoryChain that is to be used for all transactions in a batch. Each transaction is handled by a TransactionApplierFacade which wraps the individual TransactionAppliers returned by the wrapped TransactionApplierFactorys.

        public void flushAndForce​(IOLimiter limiter,
                          PageCursorTracer cursorTracer)
                   throws IOException
        Description copied from interface: StorageEngine
        Flushes and forces all changes down to underlying storage. This is a blocking call and when it returns all changes applied to this storage engine will be durable.
